      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDSTAR VOGUE (1) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing sixth (20.59) in a Grade 6 at this track. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Has ability and looks hard to stop. GO GO POTATO (7) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (20.38) last time in a Grade 6 at this track. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Must be included in calculations. SMASHING DOUBLE (2) turned in a plain run last time when seventh at this track over 352m behind Electric Luxe (20.63) in a Grade 6. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Expected to feature in the finish. YAPPING ACES (4) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at her latest outing at this circuit.",
